                The system begins playing syncronously with the other instruments via UDP signals, 
                and drives 18 DC motors bidirectionally using the 15 GPIO pins of a NodeMCU. 
                The majority of the circuit shown is a combination of demultiplexers and hex inverters designed
                to drive three states (clockwise, counterclockwise, off) of 18 motors with this limited number of GPIO pins. 
                <br>
                This project was built with two other students as part of a summer robotics course (ESAP Robotics 2019) for credit at the University of Pennsylvania.

